22/04/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Emil Boc will temporarily lead the labour ministry, President Traian Basescu decided on Thursday (April 21st), following the resignation of Ioan Botis as minister amid suspected conflict of interest.
The actual selection of a new minister will be postponed until after the Easter holidays.
The favourite, according to local media, is Liberal Democratic Party lawmaker Claudia Boghicevici, who is also vice-president of the labour committee within the Deputies Chamber.
(Hotnews.ro, Ziare, Realitatea, Ziarul Financiar, Adevarul - 21/04/11)
